Detailed Description

cvmx_sli_pkt_in_int

This register specifies which input packets rings are interrupting because of done counts. A bit set in this interrupt register will set a corresponding bit in SLI_PKT_INT which can cause a MSI-X interrupt. When read by a function, this register informs which rings owned by the function (0 to N, N as large as 63) have this interrupt pending. SLI_PKT_IN_INT conditions can cause MSI-X interrupts, but do not cause any SLI_MAC()_PF()_INT_SUM bit to set, and cannot cause INTA/B/C/D nor MSI interrupts.
